      "content": "St John's wort is a natural remedy, but it can still interact with your medication. The jitteriness or heart racing you mentioned is a potential side effect, but it's not a major concern. Just make sure to monitor how you feel and keep your doctor in the loop. If you experience any discomfort, you can always adjust the dosage or stop taking it. Remember, it's always better to be safe than sorry, so keep an eye on your body and don't hesitate to reach out to a healthcare professional if you have any concerns.",
